 :automagically: /aw-toh-maj'i-klee/ adv. Automatically, but in a way that,
for some reason (typically because it is too complicated, or too ugly, or
perhaps even too trivial), the speaker doesn't feel like explaining to you.
see {magic}. "The C-INTERCAL compiler generates C, then automagically invokes
`cc(1)' to produce an executable."